c: 33
v: 13
t: "And when a party among them said: \"You men of Yathrib (the Prophet’s old town)! You cannot withstand (the attack), so go back!\" And a group of them asked the Prophet to be excused (to go away), saying: \"Truly, our houses are bare and in danger,\" even though they were not in (any) danger: They wanted nothing but to run away (from fighting)"